<h2>Best HVAC Systems for Allentown Climate</h2>
<p>For Allentown's cold climate, dual-fuel systems or high-efficiency heat pumps with backup heating are optimal choices. Look for heat pumps rated for cold climate performance with HSPF ratings of 9.0 or higher and SEER ratings of at least 16. Modern cold-climate heat pumps can effectively heat homes down to -5¬∞F, making them viable for most Allentown winter conditions. However, a backup natural gas furnace or electric resistance heating is recommended for extreme cold snaps. Gas furnaces should have AFUE ratings of 90% or higher, while air conditioners should meet minimum 16 SEER standards, though 18 SEER systems provide better long-term value given PPL's electricity rates. Since heating demands far exceed cooling needs in Allentown, prioritize heating efficiency over cooling efficiency when making equipment selections.</p>

