<p>Allentown residents can access multiple rebate programs to offset HVAC installation costs. Federal tax credits offer 30% of installation costs up to specific limits for heat pumps, with no cap through 2032 under the Inflation Reduction Act. Pennsylvania's Alternative Energy Portfolio Standard provides additional incentives for high-efficiency systems. PPL offers rebates up to \$400 for ENERGY STAR qualified heat pumps and up to \$300 for central air conditioners meeting efficiency requirements. The utility also provides rebates for smart thermostats (\$50-100) and duct sealing services. Low-income households may qualify for additional weatherization assistance through Lehigh County programs. Combined federal, state, and utility incentives can reduce total system costs by \$2,000-\$4,500, significantly improving payback periods for high-efficiency equipment.</p>

